<title>BRAZIL: Brazil to see record grains/oilseeds crop - Safras.</title>
<headline>Brazil to see record grains/oilseeds crop - Safras.</headline>
<dateline>RIO DE JANEIRO 1997-03-31</dateline>
<text>
<p>Brazil's grains and oilseed crop should reach 77.95 million tonnes in 1997, up six percent from 73.44 million tonnes in 1996, independent consultants Safras e Mercado said in its weekly newsletter.</p>
<p>If correct, this year's crop will be above the previous record of 76.80 million tonnes harvested in 1995, it added.</p>
<p>The higher forecast is linked to the increased area of the two main crops - soybeans and corn - and to higher productivity.</p>
<p>One other positive factor has been the re-negotiation of producer debt, Safras said.</p>
<p>Principal crops included in the Safras e Mercado forecast were as follows in 1,000 tonnes.</p>
<p> CROP		    1997		1996	    PCT CHANGE</p>
<p> Rice		   9,733	    10,153	     -4</p>
<p> Oats		     190		 197	     -4</p>
<p> Barley		   220		 219		0</p>
<p> Black beans	  3,000	     2,837		6</p>
<p> Corn		  34,130	    30,944	     10</p>
<p> Sorghum		  330		 313		5</p>
<p> Wheat		  2,000	     3,132	    -36</p>
<p> Palm/palm kernel     457		 387	     18</p>
<p> Soybeans	    26,884	    24,150	     11</p>
<p>((-Caroline Bulloch, Rio de Janeiro newsroom, 5521 5074151))</p>
